	Kreuter, Hans-Peter and Illing, Robert and Glavanovics, Michael and
	Kaltenbacher, Manfred},
  title = {In-situ calibration procedure for infrared microscopy temperature
	measurements},
  year = {2011},
  abstract = {To address the increased requirements regarding thermal imaging of
	microscopic structures, a novel in-situ calibration procedure is
	presented, taking into account inherent detector nonlinearities as
	well as target object emissivity variations. Detector nonlinearities
	of the microscopic infrared camera system are experimentally characterized
	and corrections are implemented accordingly to the calibration procedure.
	A physics based pixel-by-pixel fitting method correlates detected
	radiation values with the actual temperature data. Finally, the proposed
	in-situ calibration procedure is applied to a state of the art power
	semiconductor under extreme operating conditions and verified by
	comparison to local electrical temperature measurements and thermal
	finite element simulations.},
